U.S. Secretary of State to Visit Chile 
U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher is scheduled to arrive here
next Tuesday on an official three-day visit to Chile, the Chilean
Foreign Ministry said today.
Christopher will pay his first visit to Chile within the framework of
the mechanism of political consultations that exists between the two
countries, said the ministry.
During his visit, Christopher is expected to meet with President
Eduardo Frei and Foreign Minister Jose Miguel Insulza.
Christopher is scheduled to conduct his Latin America tour on February
25-March 4, which will also take him to Argentina, Brazil, El Salvador
and Trinidad and Tobago.
